<BLOCK>

<EMPH weight="bold">
Active ingredient:
</EMPH>
 nifedipine What is in your medicine Each tablet contains the active ingredient: nifedipine 10 mg
</BLOCK>


<BLOCK>
Excipients: lactose, microcrystalline cellulose, macrogol 6000, magnesium stearate, maize starch, hydroxypropylmethyl cellulose, polysorbate 80 (tween 80), talc, colourants E171, E172.
</BLOCK>

<DIV type=2>

<HEAD weight="bold" >
Presentation and contents
</HEAD>


<BLOCK>
Apricot coated, round, slightly biconvex tablets. Adipine&trade; MR 10 is available in packs of 56 tablets.
</BLOCK>


<BLOCK>
Adipine&trade; MR 10 is a medicine for the treatment of high blood pressure (hypertension) and for the prevention of coronary artery disease. It belongs to a group of drugs called calcium antagonists.
</BLOCK>

